The evaluation done originally by Nisley et al. in 1973 has been   228 1451
updated to include the results of a more recent R-matrix analysis. 228 1451
The 1973 analysis was based on a simultaneous fit of n-alpha and   228 1451
p-alpha scattering data. The newer analysis (8/06) is a multi-     228 1451
channel fit to data for the n-alpha and d-t reactions that extends 228 1451
to about 24 MeV excitation energy in the 5He system. Although this 228 1451
is well above the d+t threshold, for the present, we give n-alpha  228 1451
data only over the original range up to 20 MeV, where it is single 228 1451
channel scattering. However, the results below the d+t threshold   228 1451
are constrained by the data at higher energies through the         228 1451
R-matrix parameterization, and they are therefore better           228 1451
determined than those of a single-channel analysis.                228 1451
                                                                   228 1451
In addition, covariances (MF=33) are given for MT=2, calculated    228 1451
from the parameter covariances and derivatives from the 5He        228 1451
analysis. It should be noted that while the rank of this           228 1451
covariance matrix is 115, corresponding to the number of free      228 1451
parameters in the fit, it is given at 152 energies. This means     228 1451
that in principle some of the zero eigenvalues could have small    228 1451
negative values due to the limited precision of the numbers in the 228 1451
file and the matrix is not guaranteed to be positive semi-         228 1451
definite.                                                          228 1451
