   MT=2       ELASTIC SCATTERING CROSS SECTION                     228 1451
         ALTHOUGH THE ONLY REACTION POSSIBLE FOR NEUTRONS INCIDENT 228 1451
       ON HE-4 BELOW 20 MEV IS ELASTIC SCATTERING, THE MAJORITY    228 1451
       OF THE N-4HE DATA IS RATHER IMPRECISE.  IN ORDER TO OVER-   228 1451
       COME THIS PROBLEM, AN R-MATRIX ANALYSIS WAS PERFORMED WITH  228 1451
       A DATA SET WHICH INCLUDED NOT ONLY THE N-4HE DATA BUT ALSO  228 1451
       VERY PRECISE P-4HE DATA.  ALL THE AVAILABLE N-4HE AND P-4HE 228 1451
       DATA BELOW 20 MEV WERE CONSIDERED IN THE ANALYSIS.  SINCE   228 1451
       THE PREVIOUS EVALUATION WAS COMPLETED IN 1968, SEVERAL      228 1451
       N-4HE ELASTIC SCATTERING MEASUREMENTS HAVE BEEN DONE.  THE  228 1451
       MOST SIGNIFICANT OF THESE ARE THE LOW ENERGY NEUTRON CROSS  228 1451
       SECTION OF RORER (RO69),THE RPI TOTAL CROSS SECTION         228 1451
       MEASUREMENT (GO73), WHICH COVER THE RANGE EN=0.7-30 MEV,    228 1451
       AND THE RELATIVE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS OF MORGAN (MO68).    228 1451
       A COMPLETE LIST OF REFERENCES FOR THE N-4HE DATA USED IS    228 1451
       GIVEN BELOW.  THE P-4HE DATA WAS SELECTED TO SATISFY VERY   228 1451
       STRINGENT STATISTICAL CRITERIA AND WE BELIEVE THE POSSIBLE  228 1451
       ERRORS OF THE PREDICTED VALUES FOR THE P-4HE SCATTERING     228 1451
       TO BE LESS THAN 1.0 PER CENT.  A SIMPLE MODEL FOR THE       228 1451
       CHARGE DIFFERENCES BETWEEN THE N-4HE AND P-4HE SYSTEMS      228 1451
       WAS ASSUMED AND THE N-4HE AND P-4HE DATA SETS WERE          228 1451
       SIMULTANEOUSLY ANALYZED.  THE VALUES OF THE CROSS SECTIONS  228 1451
       AND ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS CONTAINED IN FILES 3 AND 4 ARE    228 1451
       PROBABLY ACCURATE TO WITHIN 2.0 PERCENT.                    228 1451
